latestPosts.caption:
Sharing more about my journey, experiences & what I have learnt .✨
I won my first national beauty pageant at the age of 15 and also won another crown when I was 16. Since then, I had the passion and fire within me to stand on the stage of Miss Universe India as soon as I turned 18, and I made it happen. 👑 Whenever people hear the term beauty pageants, they look at it as a gateway to Bollywood, but experiencing it all made me understand what it takes to compete in a pageant. 
• Beauty pageants are beyond what you see on social media for a girl who’s participating in it. Once you take the decision to step into this field, remember every action should be based on what effect it’s going to have on people who are looking at you and trying to relate with you. •Beauty pageants have given me a platform to reach out to people and connect with them. 
• Clarity of thoughts & clear vision The way you communicate & treat people is a form of self-expression. Pageants gave me the confidence to be fearless in terms of sharing my opinions and values both professionally & personally. 
• Understanding my personality & realising that sometimes your weakness can be your biggest strength. 
• Endless gratitude, self-acceptance, and understanding that there is always a room for growth. 
• The value of maintaining authenticity
 Throughout my journey I was told to change different things apart from grooming and look at various women in this industry; I did try to adapt it as a young teenager but soon realized that as an artist I feel my best when I embrace myself. 
• Create your own art because sometimes even mistakes lead to creativity. 
• The world is filled with endless opportunities waiting for you. Pageant experience should never be about winning. 
It’s about creating an impact and empowering individuals who doubt their potential. Gaining experience is a win
•Last but not least, remember who you are✨ There’s always going to be that one person who will laugh when you tell them about your goals & aspirations. Remember, when you look back at these people after 5 years, they will still be at the same place.
